## Summary
Implemented `word_counter.py` with a `count_words(text: str) -> dict[str, int]` function that validates input types, removes the required punctuation, normalizes case, supports multiline text, and returns per-word counts.

## Changes
- `word_counter.py`: added the production implementation for word counting.
- `test_word_counter.py`: added 10 pytest cases covering case insensitivity, punctuation stripping, multiline input, empty strings, whitespace-only text, and `TypeError` handling for non-string inputs.

## Testing
- Run `pytest test_word_counter.py`
- Run `make test`

## Notes
Assumed that “引号” includes both single quotes and double quotes, so both are stripped during normalization. Whitespace-only strings return an empty dictionary because they contain no words after splitting.
